# Portfolio Website Development Rules

## Project Overview
This is a personal portfolio website built with Next.js 14, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and Framer Motion.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 with App Router
- TypeScript for type safety
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Framer Motion for animations
- React Icons for iconography
- EmailJS for contact form
- MDX for blog posts (optional)

## Code Style Guidelines
1. Use functional components with TypeScript
2. Prefer server components unless client interactivity is needed
3. Use Tailwind classes for styling, avoid inline styles
4. Keep components small and focused
5. Use semantic HTML elements
6. Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible

## File Structure
- /app - App router pages and layouts
- /components - Reusable components
- /public - Static assets
- /lib - Utility functions and constants
- /types - TypeScript type definitions

## Component Guidelines
- Use 'use client' directive only when necessary
- Implement responsive design mobile-first
- Add proper TypeScript types for all props
- Include aria-labels for accessibility
- Use Next.js Image component for all images
- Implement loading states for async operations

## Performance Requirements
- Maintain Lighthouse score above 95
- Optimize all images with next/image
- Use dynamic imports for heavy components
- Implement proper meta tags for SEO

## Git Commit Convention
- feat: New feature
- fix: Bug fix
- style: Styling changes
- refactor: Code restructuring
- docs: Documentation updates